The paper deals with fountain codes that can overcome adversarial errors, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the codes' potential applications in distributed computing (cs.DC) and the possibility of an adversary controlling a portion of the communication paths (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the sparse structure of the codes, which could be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI).
